<item>
            <title>[LU-618] Reads are not included in IO accounting</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-618</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Writes are accounted for, but not reads. The supplied patch fixes this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems that the accounting it normally done in the kernels page writeback and readahead&lt;br/&gt;
functionality. Therefore as Lustre implements its own readahead, it must also maintain its own&lt;br/&gt;
accounting on reads (but not writes).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Previously discussed in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.lustre.org/pipermail/lustre-devel-lustre.org/2011-April/001586.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://lists.lustre.org/pipermail/lustre-devel-lustre.org/2011-April/001586.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24536&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.lustre.org/show_bug.cgi?id=24536&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
